      "id": 6819,
      "name": "",
      "username": "Alex",
      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2022-06-22T19:56:34.779Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Interesting you have a very positive TSB, were you taking it easy before you got sick? <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\">  It does not look like training contributed to your sickness.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d8ea26b1dcade66737a6526943815f364e948f30.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/d8ea26b1dcade66737a6526943815f364e948f30\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/d/d8ea26b1dcade66737a6526943815f364e948f30_2_690x475.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"uWUNBL2kdVt2V2eZbk74PqOPVGo\" width=\"690\" height=\"475\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/d/d8ea26b1dcade66737a6526943815f364e948f30_2_690x475.jpeg, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d8ea26b1dcade66737a6526943815f364e948f30.jpeg 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d8ea26b1dcade66737a6526943815f364e948f30.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/2X/d/d8ea26b1dcade66737a6526943815f364e948f30_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">980\u00d7676 112 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>So yes I would say a week off (now), if you are feeling good then do an easy week of about 200 TSS or so, maybe delay your easy rides until later in the week if necessary\u2026 Then I would just do your last recovery week again and continue your plan (so really 3-weeks behind schedule.  End your build period 3-weeks early and start your peak plan.  That is just rough idea as it might need more detailed tweaking based on how you feel and what makes sense to you.</p>",
