      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2022-06-23T14:12:19.340Z",
      "cooked": "<p>No positive TSB will actually put you in better \u201cform\u201d so you will perform well, but you are also slowly loosing fitness in a positive TSB state so you don\u2019t want to spend too much time there.  I don\u2019t take these numbers too seriously, but just look at the basic perspective.  Super deep negative TSB for too long and feeling symptoms of this (risk of illness) vs closer to zero vs losing fitness and performing well at approximately zero to positive.</p>",
